  "body": "I just tried creating a pool in the toolbox and it failed:\r\n```\r\nroot@rook-tools:/#  rookctl pool create --name rbd\r\nfailed to create new pool 'rbd': HTTP status code 500 for query pool: ''\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe API pod logs show that the pool could not be created because the specified CRUSH rule did not exist:\r\n```\r\n2017-11-03 15:36:07.835408 I | api: 44ab1caa-72e9-40dd-86f0-bc8932a88486\tPOST\t/pool\tCreatePool\t(start)\r\n2017-11-03 15:36:07.836628 I | exec: Running command: ceph osd pool create rbd 0 replicated rbd --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/823890396\r\n2017-11-03 15:36:08.052158 I | exec: Error ENOENT: specified rule rbd doesn't exist\r\n2017-11-03 15:36:08.052380 E | api: failed to create new pool 'rbd'. failed to create pool rbd. exit status 2\r\n2017-11-03 15:36:08.052429 I | api: 44ab1caa-72e9-40dd-86f0-bc8932a88486\tPOST\t/pool\tCreatePool\t500 Internal Server Error\t217.020771ms\r\n```",
